w of how dystopian fiction constantly adapts to - and reflects on - the actual world.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aDystopia 0aElectronic books. 0aScience fiction. 4aDystopia. 4aScience Fiction. 4aspatial turn. 4aurban. 70(DE-601)1051598670(DE-588)4202262-9aAnti-Utopie2gnd 70(DE-601)1057303940(DE-588)4126697-3aStadtgMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-601)1063387490(DE-588)4014777-0aEnglisch2gnd 70(DE-601)2258304850(DE-588)4447177-4aGeografiegMotiv2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105339650 cprintz978311053391040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110535853423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110535853.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017